{{Infobox journal | title = Australian Journal of Politics and History | cover = Australian Journal of Politics and History.jpg | editor = Matt McDonald, Andrew Bonnell | discipline = [[politics]], [[History]] | peer-reviewed = | language = | formernames = | abbreviation = Aust. J. Politics Hist. | publisher = [[Wiley-Blackwell]] for the School of Political Science & International Studies and the School of Historical & Philosophical Inquiry at the [[University of Queensland]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1955–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/journal/10.1111/(ISSN)1467-8497 | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = | link2-name = | RSS = | atom = | JSTOR = | OCLC = | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 0004-9522 | eISSN = 1467-8497 | boxwidth = }} The '''''Australian Journal of Politics and History''''' is an [[academic journal]] that includes articles about [[history]], [[political studies]], and [[International relations|international affairs]], concentrating on [[Australia]], the [[Asia-Pacific]] region, and modern [[Europe]]. It was established in 1955 and was published triennially until 1997. In 1998 it began publishing quarterly. It is currently edited by Andrew Bonnell and Matt McDonald, both at the University of Queensland. It is published by [[Wiley-Blackwell]].
