{{Infobox journal | title = Semiotics: Yearbook of the Semiotic Society of America | cover = | editor = Jamin Pelkey | language = English | discipline = [[semiotics]] | formernames = | abbreviation = Semiotics | publisher = [[Philosophy Documentation Center]] | country = | frequency = Annual | history = 1980–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = https://www.pdcnet.org/cpsem | link2 = https://www.pdcnet.org/cpsem/toc | link2-name = Online access | JSTOR = | OCLC = 10212912 | LCCN = 84640162 | CODEN = | ISSN = 0742-7611 | eISSN = 2166-6717 }}
'''''Semiotics: Yearbook of the Semiotic Society of America''''' is an annual series that publishes a selection of the [[peer review|peer-reviewed]] papers presented at the society’s annual conference. The content and thematic focus of each volume varies based on the program of the annual meeting. Notable contributors include [[Marcel Danesi]], [[John Deely]], [[Stephanie Walsh Matthews]], [[Augusto Ponzio]], and [[Thomas Sebeok]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pdcnet.org/cpsem/toc|title=Tables of contents|accessdate=16 September 2016|work=Semiotics: The Proceedings of the Semiotic Society of America}}</ref>
The [[Semiotic Society of America]] is an [[interdisciplinarity|interdisciplinary]] [[professional association]] that supports the study of signs and sign-systems. In addition to this series the society also publishes ''[[The American Journal of Semiotics]]''. All volumes of both publications are available online from the [[Philosophy Documentation Center]].
